posts.raw_content: The point of “cloture” (wasn’t a thing until 1917) was actually to SPEED UP passage of bills in the senate. It was to END debate quickly when there was a clear majority (a 60-40 vote). It was passed by PROGRESSIVES and Woodrow Wilson to force things through the senate more quickly. It existed alongside the original filibuster, which was merely a way for a minority to SLOW passage of bills, not stop them. When there was not a massive majority in favor (like a 51-49 vote). It is purely lazy politicians that decided to treat “cloture” as some divine senate rule that has to be followed at all times. It’s not in the constitution. It’s not in federal law. It’s the same as being in elementary school and not being able to write on a desk, a fucking meaningless rule that will inevitably be ignored down the line when people find out there is no punishment for it. That has held the country hostage for decades. Seemingly solely because politicians are cowards and lazy bums. Every elected Democrat has said they will vote to end the filibuster permanently, fetterman included btw, not one has come out against that. I don’t ever want to hear the argument that “but democrats will get rid of the filibuster”. They have ALL promised to do that already. All of them. Find me one federal level Democrat in office that is explicitly against ending the filibuster. Standing or talking filibuster (the traditional one where they have to endlessly talk) should be kept, I think that’s inherently conservative. The senate is supposed to move slowly, not come to a halt.
